Rating: 4
I have made this three times. It's easy to do and always tastes amazing. The following changes were made: 1) I lightly coated the snapper chunks with flour and sauteed them first in the olive oil and set them aside. I added them at the end with the parsley and basil, otherwise the fish just dissolves. 2) I use vinho verde - it gives the broth a lighter more fragrant flavor 3) I ditched the green bell pepper and used 3 or 4 small finely chopped serrano chiles (seeded). This gives the broth a teensy kick which even the "heat averse" can appreciate. This dish is well worth the (minimal) effort and (modest) cost. Enjoy!

